waitForSISCalls

public boolean waitForSISCalls(String[] parameters)
wait for a SIS call on the SISServer

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters. parameters[0] argument is always the method name, parameters[1] argument is the number of calls received total since starting the SISServer If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.

setOverrideNumber

public boolean setOverrideNumber(String[] parameters)
Set the number that is used as input for the decoding of parameters instead of the supplied phone number. Example 41790000009.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters. parameters[0] argument is always the method name, parameters[1] the override number for the SISServer If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
See Also:
SubscriberInformationServiceImpl.setOverrideNumber(String)
